==English==

===Etymology===
*From the Russian word for "[[desert]]."

===Noun===
'''poustinia''' (plural: poustinias)

#In [[Christian]] [[spirituality]], a small sparsely furnished cabin or room where a person goes to [[fast]] and [[pray]], but which is less austere than a [[hermitage]].

====Quotations====
#'''1975''': Yes, that "doing something more" can be the '''poustinia''': an entry into the desert, a lonely place, a silent place, where one can lift the two arms of prayer and penance to God in atonement, intercession, reparation for one's sins and those of one's brothers.... To go into the '''poustinia''' means to listen to God. It means entering into ''[[kenosis]]''&mdash;the emptying of oneself. &mdash; ''Poustinia'', [[w:Catherine Doherty|Catherine Doherty]]

